This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the development of embeddings for spoken language. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech data. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves speaker comparison and clustering. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a Siamese convolutional neural network architecture for training. Finally, it could belong to cs.SD again as it evaluates the embeddings on acoustic models.
